This paper deals with wireless network capacity, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-fields. The use of power control and interference models suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The focus on approximation algorithms and centralized complexity analysis suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the use of metric spaces suggests that it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
